    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen we conceal a text with a char that has a display width larger than one (like an emoji), the cursor position is not right.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`nvim --clean`\r\n`:edit test.txt`\r\nType: `:wrench: test`\r\n`:lua vim.fn.matchadd(\"Conceal\", \":wrench:\", 0, 12, { conceal = \"ðŸ”§\" })`\r\n`:set conceallevel=1`\r\n`:set concealcursor=ni`\r\nType `$`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe cursor should be positioned at the end of the line, at the character `t`. Instead, it is positioned at the character `s`. Probably, the algorithm is assuming that the conceal char display width is always 1, which is not the case here.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.4\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nYes, Vim 9.0.1544\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.0\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niTerm2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
